description.narrative: The Government of Angola has increased national capacity to provide access and quality of justice services for children in contact with the law (perpetrators, survivors, witnesses and children third parties in judiciary proceedings),which contributes to Access To Justice, Justice For Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2019, the most vulnerable children and adolescents will benefit from accessible, equitable, affordable and high quality child protection services, including the birth registration, response to violence, abuse, exploitation and neglect and child-friendly justice
